20/04/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Parliament rejected late on Monday (April 19th) a motion to remove Justice Minister Mihajlo Manevski. The vote was 16 in favour, 65 against. The opposition Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia had accused the minister of nepotism, financial irregularities in the justice ministry as well as blaming him for poor prison conditions. Manevski rejected all accusations as groundless. (A1, Makfax, Alsat, MIA - 20/04/10)
